    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <h3><a name="Description"></a><b>Description</b></h3>

<p>When an announcement is activated or deactivated from the panel, the change is not reflected instantly in the iOS app. Users need to minimize or close the app and reopen it (or manually refresh) to see the updated status. However, on Android, the update is reflected instantly without any extra steps.</p>

<h3><a name="StepstoReproduce"></a><b>Steps to Reproduce</b></h3>

<ol>
	<li>Open the panel and activate or deactivate any announcement</li>
	<li>Open the FP Agent App on an iOS device</li>
	<li>Go to the Announcements section</li>
	<li>Observe the announcement status</li>
	<li>Minimize or close the app and reopen it (or refresh)</li>
	<li>Check the announcement status again</li>
</ol>


<h3><a name="ExpectedResult"></a><b>Expected Result</b></h3>

<p>Announcement status changes should reflect instantly in the iOS app without needing to restart or refresh.</p>

<h3><a name="ActualResult"></a><b>Actual Result</b></h3>

<p>Changes are not updated instantly; users must reopen or refresh the app to see updates.</p>

<h3><a name="Severity"></a><b>Severity</b></h3>

<p>Medium</p>
            <br/>
